items.title: Mexico Economy Narrowly Dodges Recession Amid US Trade Chaos
items.description: (Bloomberg) -- Mexico’s economy expanded slightly in the first quarter on a jump in agricultural output, allowing President Claudia Sheinbaum to avoid recession as she steers the nation through an unpredictable US tariff policy.
